RVM Commands:

1] rvm gemset list # To list available gemsets for current ruby version.

   rvm gemset list_all # To list available gemsets of all installed ruby versions.

2] rvm gemset create test_project # Creeates the gemset called test_project
   
   rvm gemset use create test_project # To change to gemset we wish to use

3] rvm use 2.0.0@test_project # To change ruby version and gemset at once in this eg, we use ruby

   version 2.0.0 and gemset test_project

4] gem install tictactoe -v 0.0.4 # installs gemset named tictactoe

5] rvm get stable # Updates stable version of RVM

   rvm get head # Updates Latest version of RVM

